Nameless Shadow						KEY:Rogue Archetype ~ Nameless Shadow												CATEGORY:Archetype			TYPE:Archetype.RogueArchetype																		PRECLASS:1,Rogue=1		PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Rogue Archetype ~ Nameless Shadow],[!PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Rogue_Archetype_Trapfinding=True,Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent2=True,Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent4=True,Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent6=True,Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent8=True,Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent10=True,Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent14=True,Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent18=True]							DESC:Where bandits and tyrants prey on merchants and caravans, the nameless shadow preys on bandits and tyrants. Posing as mundane merchants or other harmless travelers, these assassins can hide both within darkness and in the anonymity of a seemingly unimportant crowd.																																																																																																																ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Nameless Shadow ~ Harmless Guise|PRECLASS:1,Rogue=1		ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Nameless Shadow ~ Face in the Crowd|PRECLASS:1,Rogue=4																																																																																																																																																															COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.30																FACT:Rogue_Archetype_Trapfinding|true	FACT:Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent2|true	FACT:Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent4|true	FACT:Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent6|true	FACT:Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent8|true	FACT:Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent10|true	FACT:Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent14|true	FACT:Rogue_Archetype_RogueTalent18|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_Trapfinding|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_RogueTalent2|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_RogueTalent4|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_RogueTalent6|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_RogueTalent8|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_RogueTalent10|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_RogueTalent14|true	FACT:Rogue_CF_RogueTalent18|true

Harmless Guise						KEY:Nameless Shadow ~ Harmless Guise												CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Features.NamelessShadowClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																															DESC:A nameless shadow gains the dual identity and seamless guise vigilante class features, with the following restrictions. Her social identity must be that of a mundane and nonthreatening member of society, such as a farmer or a merchant. Additionally, when a nameless shadow attacks a foe while in a social or mundane identity, her target takes a –2 penalty to AC for the purpose of resolving that attack. This use of harmless guise forces the nameless shadow into her vigilante identity after the attack is completed, and the target (if it survives) then becomes aware of the nameless shadow's secret. This ability cannot be used on targets that are aware of the nameless shadow's dual identity.					ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Nameless Shadow ~ Dual Identity|Nameless Shadow ~ Seamless Guise		ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Social Talent ~ Many Guises|PRECLASS:1,Rogue=6	ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Social Talent ~ Quick Change|PRECLASS:1,Rogue=8		ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Social Talent ~ Everyman|PRECLASS:1,Rogue=14		ABILITY:Special Ability|VIRTUAL|Social Talent ~ Any Guise|PRECLASS:1,Rogue=18																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.30
Face in the Crowd					KEY:Nameless Shadow ~ Face in the Crowd												CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Features.NamelessShadowClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																															DESC:so long as there are at least 10 other nonhostile creatures within 30 feet of her, a nameless shadow can use Bluff or Disguise in place of Stealth to hide or for sniping.		DESC: She can use this ability to hide within a crowd even if she is being observed.|PRECLASS:1,Rogue=8																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.30
Dual Identity						KEY:Nameless Shadow ~ Dual Identity													CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Features.NamelessShadowClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																															DESC:A nameless shadow hides his true identity, allowing him to move about social circles and nobility without carrying the stigma of his ruthless actions. In effect, the nameless shadow has two identities: one is a polite member of society while the other is a skilled and cunning warrior. To keep up this charade, the nameless shadow usually has two names: his true name, used in polite company, and his nameless shadow name, used to strike fear in the hearts of those who oppose him. Knowledge checks about one do not reveal information about the other, unless the nameless shadow's true identity revealed to the world at large. The nameless shadow can start each day in either of his identities, referred to simply as social or nameless shadow. Changing from one identity to another takes 1 minute and must be done out of sight from other creatures to preserve the nameless shadow's secret. Changing identities is more than just changing outfits and clothing (although that is certainly a part of it); the process often also involves applying make-up, altering his hair, and adjusting other personal effects. Furthermore, the change is as much a state of mind as of body, so items such as a hat of disguise and similar spells and effects that change the user's appearance do not reduce the time required to change identities. Most social talents require the nameless shadow to be in his social identity, but a nameless shadow who uses nameless shadow talents in his social identity risks exposing his secret. Despite being a single person, a nameless shadow's dual nature allows him to have two alignments, one for each of his identities. When in an identity, he is treated as having that identity's alignment for all spells, magic items, and abilities that rely on alignment. For the purpose of meeting a qualification for a feat, class, or any ability, he is only eligible if both of his alignments meet the requirements. A nameless shadow's two alignments cannot be more than one step from each other on a single alignment axis. For example, a nameless shadow with a lawful neutral social identity could have a nameless shadow identity that is lawful good, lawful neutral, lawful evil, neutral, neutral good, or neutral evil. If a nameless shadow is the target of an effect that would change his alignment, it changes both of his alignments to the new alignment. Any attempts to scry or otherwise locate the nameless shadow work only if the nameless shadow is currently in the identity the creature is attempting to locate (or if the creature knows that the two identities are the same individual). Otherwise, the spell or effect has no effect, revealing nothing but darkness, as if the target were invalid or did not exist.
Seamless Guise						KEY:Nameless Shadow ~ Seamless Guise												CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Features.NamelessShadowClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																																																																																																						DEFINE:SeamlessGuiseBonus|0			DESC:A nameless shadow knows how to behave in a way that appears perfectly proper and normal for his current identity. Should anyone suspect him of being anything other than what he appears to be while either in his social or nameless shadow identity, he can attempt a Disguise check with a +%1 circumstance bonus to appear as his current identity, and not as his other identity.|SeamlessGuiseBonus																																																																																																																																																																																																																																										BONUS:VAR|SeamlessGuiseBonus|20

